column1: #  The water-quality data provided herein are the principal stream-water data summarized in USGS
#  Circular 1291, Pesticides in the Nation's Streams and Ground  Water, 1992-2001: The Quality
#  Analytical data for 75 pesticides and 8 degradates at 186 stream-water sampling sites are provided
#  in this tab-delimited data file. Stream-water sites in 51 Study Units were selected in accordance
#  with the NAWQA national design strategy. Sites were classified into four land-use groups (agriculture,
#  urban, undeveloped, or mixed) on the basis of national land-use data sets and information on point
#  sources and other influences on water quality. Pesticide samples were collected for one or more years
#  at each site using a combination of fixed-interval and extreme-flow sampling. In general, two to four
#  samples were collected each month during seasonal periods of high pesticide use and one sample was
#  collected each month during other periods. A one-year period of pesticide data was selected for each
#  site (the one-year period with the most samples and analytes) to characterize the annual distribution
#  of pesticide concentrations. The selected one-year periods of data are provided in this data file.
#  A detailed discussion of methods and approaches used for pesticides in stream water for Circular 1291,
#  including site selection, land-use classification, sample-collection, laboratory analysis, and data
#  processing and analysis is presented in Appendix 8.
#  Pesticide names, CAS numbers, and other characteristics are presented in Appendix 1A.
#  Characteristics of stream-water sampling sites are presented in Appendix 5.
#  METADATA Basic documentation of dataset elements:
#           Note: The row in the data file that follows the row of variable names describes the
#                 width of the field and the data type. S or s indicates a text variable,
#                 D or d indicates a date variable, and N or n indicates a numeric variable.
#                 For example: 15s indicates a 0- to 15-character text variable whereas
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#            Note: PSTAID should be used for data analysis. STAID is the
#                  actual location of the sample. For 181 of 186 sites,
#                  PSTAID is equal to STAID for all samples. STAID not
#                  equal to PSTAID occurs where the location of sample
#                  collection changed during the period of data collection,
#                  but is considered equivalent to PSTAID.
#       Attribute description: Date of sample, YYYY.MM.DD
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#       Attribute description: Purpose of site visit for sample collection
#       Source: Value assigned based on value of NWIS parameter code 50280,
#               NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#       Attribute description: Drainage basin land use class
#                Ag     Greater than 50% agricultural land and less than or equal to 5% urban land
#                Undev  Less than or equal to 25% agricultural land and less than or equal to 5% urban land
#                Urban  Greater than 25% urban land and less than or equal to 25 % agricultural land
#                Mixed  All other combinations of land use
#       Attribute description: Name of data collection station (PSTAID)
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002, updated by jdmartin
#       Attribute description: NAWQA Study Unit identifier
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#                almn   Allegheny and Monongahela River Basins
#                conn   Connecticut, Housatonic, and Thames River Basins
#                leri   Lake Erie-Lake Saint Clair Drainages
#                linj   Long Island-New Jersey Coastal Drainages
#                miam   Great and Little Miami River Basins
#                nvbr   Las Vegas Valley Area and the Carson and Truckee River Basins
#                redn   Red River of the North Basin
#                sant   Santee River Basin and Coastal Drainages
#       Attribute description: Start date of selected 1-year period of water-quality data, YYYY.MM.DD
#       Source: Time period selected by jdmartin
#       Attribute label: Rnnnnn (All variables of the form Rnnnnn, where nnnnn is the 5-digit parameter
#                         code used to identify variables in the USGS National Water Information System)
#       Attribute description: Remark code associated with each parameter value
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#                <        Not Detected. Value reported as less than the Maximum Long-Term Method Detection
#                E        Detected. Concentration is estimated. Estimated concentration may result from
#                          1. The compound is characterized as a "poor performer" in the method on the
#                             basis of laboratory QC samples. In general compounds with less than 60 %
#                             recovery, greater than 120 % recovery, or greater than 25 % relative standard
#                             deviation of recovery are considered poor performers. All detections of
#                          2. The compound was detected at a concentration less than the reporting level
#                             or less than the lowest calibration standard.
#                          3. The sample was diluted to bring the concentration into the calibration range.
#       Attribute label: Pnnnnn (All variables of the form Pnnnnn, where nnnnn is the 5-digit parameter
#                         code used to identify variables in the USGS National Water Information System)
#       Attribute description: Value of chemical analysis or streamflow measurement
#       Source: NAWQA Data Warehouse water-quality data retrieval 3-29-2002
#       Attribute subdescription: Parameter codes, names, and units of measurement
#               P00060           Daily mean streamflow      Cubic feet per second
#               P00061           Instantaneous streamflow   Cubic feet per second
#               P49304           Dacthal monoacid           Micrograms per liter
#               P49313           Aldicarb sulfone           Micrograms per liter
#               P49314           Aldicarb sulfoxide         Micrograms per liter
#               P61188           Chloramben methyl ester    Micrograms per liter
